cs.AR, cs.OS, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.PF

This paper deals with memory scheduling in heterogeneous systems with hardware accelerators, which involves aspects of computer architecture, operating systems, and system-level design. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AR (Architecture), followed by cs.OS (Operating Systems) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses memory access characteristics and scheduling policies, which are relevant to the categories cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.PF (Performance).
